Marketing  Media:
   The Journal's Crovitz,
   Geyelin Win Awards
   For Legal Coverage
Mr. Crovitz, 33 years old, was recognized for his "Rule of
Law" opinion column discussing, among other topics, the
Clarence Thomas nomination, prosecutorial abuses on Wall
Street, and the Iran-Contra independent counsel.
   Milo Geyelin, a member of the Journal's New York bureau,
received a certificate of merit in the daily newspaper
continuing-coverage category.
   Mr. Geyelin, 37, was honored for a variety of stories on
issues such as crowded court dockets, sexual harassment,
trends in legal education, and lawyers' relationships with
their clients.
   The Journal is published by Dow Jones  Co.